IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Amy Biehl High School partners with community resources to raise funds to support Amy Biehl High School's needs in fulfilling their mission to graduate diverse learners and leaders who demonstrate the intellectual, social, and ethical habits to positively impact their communities.
IRS990.MissionDesc: The Amy Biehl High School Foundation supports the mission of Amy Biehl High School. Amy Biehl High School was founded in the spirit of Amy Biehl, a young scholar dedicated to social justice and service. We partner with community resources to graduate diverse learners and leaders who demonstrate the intellectual, social, and ethical habits to positively impact their communities. Our graduates are civic-minded, college-bound and career-ready.
IRS990.Desc: Providing funding to Amy Biehl High School for enrichment programs, extended day and interim school, service programs, and salary support. 300 students served.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Angel Fund which helps students facing economic hardships by providing funding for dual enrollment textbooks, college entrance exams, college trips, and other college preparatory expenses.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The IRS Form 990 is given to the Board of Directors and Executive Director for review. It is approved by the Board of Directors before filing with IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Board of Directors has a written Conflict of Interest Policy which is distributed and followed by all directors.All members of the board of directors sign a conflict of interest policy statement at the annual meeting. In the event that any director has a conflict of interest that might properly limit such directors fair and impartial participation in Board deliberations or decisions, such director shall inform the Board as to the circumstances of such conflict. If those circumstances require the nonparticipation of the affected director, the Board may nonetheless request from the director any appropriate non-confidential information which might inform its decisions. No director shall cast a vote, nor take part in the final deliberation in any matter in which he or she, members of his or her immediate family or any organization to which such director has allegiance, has a personal interest that may be seen as competing with the interest of the Corporation. Any director who believes he or she may have such a conflict of interest shall so notify the Board prior to deliberation on the matter in question, and the Board shall make the final determination as to whether any director has a conflict of interest in any matter. The minutes of the Board meeting shall reflect disclosure of any conflict of interest and the recusal of the interested director.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Amy Biehl High School Foundation's Executive Director is not paid by Amy Biehl High School Foundation. He is an employee of Amy Biehl High School.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Governing documents, policies, financial statements and the IRS Form 990 are made available to the public upon request within three working days of the date the request was made.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: ABHSF and ABHS Lease Purchase Agreement:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Amy Biehl High School Foundation (ABHSF) entered into a lease purchase agreement with Amy Biehl High School (ABHS) for the 123 4th Street Albuquerque NM building. The agreement gives ABHS an option to purchase the building anytime during the lease term. Until ABHS exercise the purchase option, ABHSF has elected to account for the lease payments as rental income based on accounting rules and the language in the lease purchase agreement.
